Correlations and t-test Parameters

model_parameters.htest.Rd

Parameters of h-tests (correlations, t-tests).

# S3 method for htest
model_parameters(model, bootstrap = FALSE, ...)

Arguments

model

Object of class htest.
bootstrap

Should estimates be bootsrapped?
...

Arguments passed to or from other methods (e.g., to standardize).

Value

A data.frame of indices related to the model's parameters.

Examples

model <- cor.test(mtcars$mpg, mtcars$cyl, method = "pearson")
model_parameters(model)
#> Parameter1 | Parameter2 |     r |     t | df |      p |       95% CI |  Method
#> ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#> mtcars$mpg | mtcars$cyl | -0.85 | -8.92 | 30 | < .001 | -0.93, -0.72 | Pearson

model <- t.test(iris$Sepal.Width, iris$Sepal.Length)
model_parameters(model)
#> Parameter1       |        Parameter2 | Mean_Parameter1 | Mean_Parameter2 | Difference |      t |     df |      p |       95% CI |                  Method
#> ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#> iris$Sepal.Width | iris$Sepal.Length |            3.06 |            5.84 |       2.79 | -36.46 | 225.68 | < .001 | -2.94, -2.64 | Welch Two Sample t-test

model <- t.test(mtcars$mpg ~ mtcars$vs)
model_parameters(model)
#> Parameter  |     Group | Mean_Group1 | Mean_Group2 | Difference |     t |    df |      p |         95% CI |                  Method
#> -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#> mtcars$mpg | mtcars$vs |       16.62 |       24.56 |       7.94 | -4.67 | 22.72 | < .001 | -11.46,  -4.42 | Welch Two Sample t-test

model <- t.test(iris$Sepal.Width, mu = 1)
model_parameters(model)
#> Parameter        | Mean |   mu | Difference |     t |  df |      p |     95% CI |            Method
#> ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#> iris$Sepal.Width | 3.06 | 1.00 |       2.06 | 57.81 | 149 | < .001 | 2.99, 3.13 | One Sample t-test
